videoSnippet.title: Excellent Game to Improve Your Day | Petrosian vs Martirosyan | Aeroflot (2019)
videoSnippet.description:
The tournament was won by  Kaido Kulaots, check here https://chess24.com/en/embed-tournament/aeroflot-open-2019

Follow me on Instagram for extra content https://www.instagram.com/agadmator/

Petrosian, Tigran L. (ARM) - Martirosyan, Haik M. (ARM)
17th Aeroflot Open (Group A) (2019), Moscow, rd 9, Feb-27
Giuoco Piano Game (C50)

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. d3 Nf6 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 a6 7. a4 d6 8. c3 Ba7 9. O-O Qe7 10. Nbd2 g5 11. Bg3 Nd7 12. Bd5 h5 13. h4 g4 14. Ne1 Nf8 15. d4 Ng6 16. Nc4 exd4 17. Nd3 Nce5 18. cxd4 Nxc4 19. Bxc4 Bxd4 20. Nf4 c5 21. Nxg6 fxg6 22. b4 Be6 23. bxc5 dxc5 24. Bxe6 Qxe6 25. Rb1 b6 26. Qb3 c4 27. Qb4 Bc5 28. Qc3 O-O 29. Rfc1 Rad8 30. Rc2 Rd4 31. Re1 b5 32. axb5 axb5 33. Qa5 Qc6 34. Rb1 b4 35. Rxb4 Bxb4 36. Qxb4 Qxe4 37. Ra2 Qe6 38. Kh2 Rd7 39. Rc2 Rc8 40. Qc3 Rd3 41. Qa5 Rd1 42. Qg5 c3 43. Qh6 Qf5 44. Re2 c2 45. Be5 Rh1+ 46. Kg3 Rh3+
To those of you who read the description: You are an excellent subscriber! :)

The 17th Aeroflot Open runs from 19-27 February 2019 in the Cosmos Hotel in Moscow. The A Open, for players rated 2550+ and talented juniors, sees Wei Yi as top-seed fighting for the €18,000 first prize and a place in the Dortmund 2019 Supertournament, while the total prize fund for the three opens and blitz is €140,000.

Players receive 90 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 30 minutes to the end of the game, plus a 30-second increment starting from move one. The event is sponsored by Aeroflot and organised by the Russian Chess Federation in cooperation with the Association of Chess Federations. Official website: acfed.ru
